-- Turkey’s Vestel Sees Gulf Interest for Smart Tablets, AA Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-03T08:52:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/turkey-s-vestel-sees-gulf-interest-for-smart-tablets-aa-says.html
Vestel Elektronik Sanayi & Ticaret AS (VESTL) 
is seeing demand from the  Middle East  for electronic tablets
it’s developing for use in Turkish classrooms, Chairman Omer Yungul told the state-run Anatolia news agency.  The company has begun negotiations to sell the tablets to
foreign countries and aims to make Turkey a production hub for
smart boards and tablet computers, Yungul was quoted by AA as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
